<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.199531>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Danakilia dinicolai, holotype, MSNM 4888, male, 96.4 mm SL, Lake Abaeded, Eritrea." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/199531/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.199533>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Danakilia dinicolai (a) wild caught female and (b) wild caught male. Specimens not preserved or measured." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/199533/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.199532>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Lower pharyngeal jaw (dorsal, posterior and lateral views), left mandible and isolated tooth in (a) Danakilia dinicolai, (b) Danakilia franchettii, (c) Iranocichla hormuzensis. Elements drawn in corresponding scale for each species. Posterior neurocranium and anterior vertebral elements, arrows indicate inferior vertebral apophysis of (d) Iranocichla hormuzensis." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/199532/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.199534>
